it'll also help you with platform deals.

173
00:08:46,081 --> 00:08:49,321
Generally speaking, you want to make a polished prototype.

174
00:08:49,341 --> 00:08:50,582
You want to do marketing first,

175
00:08:50,602 --> 00:08:51,702
which was a talk I just did,

176
00:08:51,742 --> 00:08:53,883
which basically just means make it pretty

177
00:08:53,943 --> 00:08:55,163
and make it look like a complete game

178
00:08:55,203 --> 00:08:56,503
before you start showing to other people

179
00:08:56,543 --> 00:08:57,263
so that they can...

180
00:08:58,060 --> 00:09:00,601
kind of anchor in the idea that this is a complete game,

181
00:09:00,661 --> 00:09:03,101
it's huge and big, instead of seeing the shitty prototype

182
00:09:03,161 --> 00:09:04,942
and having to imagine how this is going

183
00:09:04,962 --> 00:09:06,022
to become something larger.

184
00:09:07,362 --> 00:09:09,103
It also helps before you have a deal,

185
00:09:09,123 --> 00:09:10,203
if you've got some amount of buzz.

186
00:09:10,443 --> 00:09:11,783
That doesn't mean you have to have a lot of buzz,

187
00:09:11,803 --> 00:09:13,804
but if you've at least announced something that looks pretty

188
00:09:14,224 --> 00:09:16,724
and looks like a complete game, even if it very much isn't,

189
00:09:18,085 --> 00:09:20,685
you'll have an easier time talking to platforms

190
00:09:20,725 --> 00:09:22,826
because you can say, look at this thing, which theoretically

191
00:09:22,866 --> 00:09:24,606
exists, and you understand it, instead of.

192
00:09:25,067 --> 00:09:28,530
look at these two cubes which are awkwardly bumping into each other, I promise this is

193
00:09:28,570 --> 00:09:35,676
going to be a great game. Give me $300,000. That's a much harder conversation. Also, platform fit

194
00:09:35,716 --> 00:09:42,702
matters. So obviously, what Apple cares about is different from what Xbox cares about. Sony,

195
00:09:42,822 --> 00:09:46,125
you might think they're identical to Xbox, but no, what the kind of game that Sony cares about

196
00:09:46,185 --> 00:09:51,009
is very different from the kind of game Xbox cares about. They all have their own style and vibe.

197
00:09:51,588 --> 00:09:54,588
and you kind of need to pick your targets well.

198
00:09:54,808 --> 00:09:56,349
That doesn't mean that you shouldn't like throw a wide net

199
00:09:56,369 --> 00:09:59,089
and try everyone, but you're more likely to get

200
00:09:59,129 --> 00:10:00,850
with whichever platform is closest

201
00:10:00,890 --> 00:10:02,190
to the vibe you're considering.

202
00:10:02,230 --> 00:10:03,430
So look at the other games they funded

203
00:10:04,110 --> 00:10:07,551
and try to work out what they tend to like.

204
00:10:07,791 --> 00:10:09,771
Usually you can figure something out from that.

205
00:10:10,451 --> 00:10:11,652
Now, how to make the approach.

206
00:10:12,232 --> 00:10:16,172
